CFISD kicked off the first day of the 2020-2021 school year on Sept. 8, 2020. All 92 campuses opened with enhanced safety protocols, including required face masks, desk shields, one-way hallways/stairways and limited cafeteria seating. Many students began the year with CFISD Connect remote learning.

Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 20 new photos.
September 3 at 7:19 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)
text:
Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 20 new photos.
September 3 at 7:19 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)

post_text: Cy-Fair Helping Hands is hosting a backpack and school supplies drive-thru distribution this Saturday, Aug. 29. See below for more details.
shared_text:
Patricia Hudson
August 28 at 10:43 AM ¬∑

Folks, we are here, no waiting, ready to load your car with backpacks and school supplies!!

Cy-Fair Helping Hands, located at 7520 Cherry Park Drive, Suite B, Houston 77095, will be holding a Backpacks and School Supplies Drive-Thru distribution, Saturday, August 29, 2020, 9 am -12 pm, for current clients with students attending CFISD schools. CFISD families in need of school supplies that are NOT currently clients of CFHH, are invited to come at 12 noon until 2 p.m., (or until the supply is complete). To receive school supplies, student IDs or documentation from the school is required. (No food will be distributed on Saturday).

Teachers, if you know of a CFISD family that could use some help with school supplies, please message me.

shared_text:
Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 20 new photos.
August 13 at 8:44 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 CFISD Bond referendum, Harold R. Rowe Middle School (No. 19) will be located on the Westgreen multi-campus site next to Cypress Park HS. The $58,296,000 project is being constructed by Satterfield & Pontikes Construction and is slated for an August 2020 opening date.

The building includes a three-story academic wing with a centrally located and shared commons/kitchen building, along with a new football field and running track. This second facility of the master-planned multi-campus site designed by PBK Architects, consists of approximately 252,000 square feet and is designed to accommodate up to 1,750 students.

(Photos courtesy Multivista)

shared_text:
Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 12 new photos.
August 6 at 8:53 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)

August 6 at 8:53 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)

Today, Wednesday, Aug. 5, is the deadline to fill out the ‚ÄúReturn to School Questionnaire‚Äù to select the learning option for each child that is enrolled in CFISD.

‚úÖ Log in to the Home Access Center (https://www.cfisd.net/en/parents-students/academics/grades-hac) using your PARENT login/password, NOT the STUDENT login/password.
‚úÖ Click the ‚ÄúHome‚Äù button. Select the ‚ÄúSchool Links‚Äù tab. Click the ‚ÄúReturn to School Questionnaire‚Äù.
‚úÖ You must use the parent login to see the ‚ÄúReturn to School Questionnaire‚Äù in the "School Links" tab.
‚úÖ If you do not see the ‚ÄúReturn to School Questionnaire,‚Äù you may have used the student login instead of the parent login.
‚úÖ If you do not have a parent login, please contact the Customer Care Center at 281-897-4357.

Beginning this week, parents/guardians will receive an email with instructions and a unique ‚Äúsnapcode‚Äù that will allow them to log in, review and update the information that is typically on the demographic card each year.

If your snapcode is lost or the email is not received, parents/guardians can view their student's ‚Äúsnapcode‚Äù via their Home Access Center (HAC) account. Please take a moment to go through and complete the update even if there are no changes in a student's demographic information.

post_text: The deadline to apply for P-EBT food benefits has been extended to July 31. Eligible families can apply for this one-time food benefit. Children who received free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program during the 2019-2020 school year are eligible for P-EBT. Eligible families should have received the application link from their school. Eligible families that received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits and do not have to apply. If you did not receive an application link or if you need help filling out the P-EBT application, please contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220. The public charge rule does not apply to P-EBT benefits.

shared_text:
Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 16 new photos.
June 25 at 8:44 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

post_text:
We learned a lot in Cypress-Fairbanks ISD this year despite some unexpected interruptions. You‚Äôve proven that being apart brought our community together and nothing can stop CFISD spirit!

More than ever, our community recognizes the value of public education and the critical role passionate and dedicated educators play in meeting children‚Äôs physical and emotional needs, recognizing student potential and encouraging the pursuit of dreams.

We look forward to welcoming students back to classrooms and continuing our mission of Opportunity for All! #CFISDspirit #CFISDforAll

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 28 new photos.
May 21 at 9:11 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 CFISD Bond referendum, Harold R. Rowe Middle School (No. 19) will be located on the Westgreen multi-campus site next to Cypress Park HS. The $58,296,000 project is being constructed by Satterfield & Pontikes Construction and is slated for an August 2020 opening date.

The building includes a three-story academic wing with a centrally located and shared commons/kitchen building, along with a new football field and running track. This second facility of the master-planned multi-campus site designed by PBK Architects, consists of approximately 252,000 square feet and is designed to accommodate up to 1,750 students.

(Photos courtesy Multivista)

The building includes a three-story academic wing with a centrally located and shared commons/kitchen building, along with a new football field and running track. This second facility of the master-planned multi-campus site designed by PBK Architects, consists of approximately 252,000 square feet and is designed to accommodate up to 1,750 students.

(Photos courtesy Multivista)

Congratulations Sadie Woodard Elementary for leading all CFISD schools with the highest overall participation in the Superintendent's Fun Run & Festival! Your dedication to the success of CFISD students and the mission of the Cy-Fair Educational Foundation is unparalleled, and we love your #CFISDspirit!

Congratulations, also, to our Curriculum, Instruction & Accountability department for achieving the highest number of Superintendent's Century Club members in the district! Your incredible generosity helps CFISD students to achieve their dreams, and your #CFISDspirit is shining bright!

#CFISDFunRun #CFISDforAll

post_text:
Kudos to the CFISD Cinema team and Cypress Ridge High School AVP program for putting together the first-ever Virtual CFISD Steer Lottery for the CFISD Livestock Show Association. The tradition is to gather in mass where, one by one, students draw chips from a container to determine the order they will get to select their steers. Because of social distancing, the process was modified utilizing a computer randomizer.

This is the first official event of the 2021 CFISD Livestock Show and Sale, to be held on Feb. 4-6, 2021. Congratulations and good luck to all of our students! #CFISDspirit #CFISDforAll

Parent David shares, "Ms. Bordovsky has gone out of her way to make school fun so the kids want to learn. She is easy to communicate with as a parent. My son loves her class. She has also stepped up during COVID-19 and made sure the student as well as me, the parent, totally understand what is needed. Such a joy."

Adds student Zachary: "Ms. Bordovsky makes science fun!!! I love doing the experiments with her! Happy #TeacherAppreciationWeek!!!"

Thank you Ms. Bordovsky! #CFISDspirit #ThankATeacher

Hamilton Elementary School parent Jessica shared this testimonial about teacher Tiffany May for #TeacherAppreciationWeek:

"Ms. May makes fun and educational videos for our children to watch during this pandemic. She also calls each one of her 'firsties' to see how they are doing and to see if they have any questions for her. She celebrates the kids' birthdays by making them a birthday video and she came to our house (social distanced herself) to surprise our daughter. She makes the children feel special and that is what I like about her the most. She is always thinking about their feelings!"

Thank you Ms. May! #ThankATeacher #CFISDspirit

Congratulations to Chantele Holden, CFISD‚Äôs 2020 Outstanding Mentor Liaison. VIPS Liaisons are exceptional CFISD employees who coordinate volunteer efforts on CFISD campuses.

Chantele Holden is a Mentor Liaison at Langham Creek High School. She is passionate about our mentor program and holds several events to recruit mentors to support CFISD students. Chantele knows the profound difference a mentor can make for students, and she works hard to make lasting mentor/mentee matches.

Chantele, CFISD is grateful for your dedication to CFISD volunteers and our mentor program!

post_text:
Congratulations to Mike and Pat Livingston, CFISD‚Äôs 2020 Outstanding Global Volunteers. Global Volunteers are CFISD community members who choose to invest their time and talents to support public education.

Mike and Pat Livingston are a dynamic duo who volunteer several days a week at Swenke Elementary School. The couple began volunteering when their grandchildren attended Swenke, and they‚Äôve never left. They sort lost & found items, clean out every lost lunch box, fold every article of clothing and deliver them to classroom teachers to be returned to students. They spend hours each week ensuring families don‚Äôt have to buy new items that students misplace.

Thank you, Mike and Pat! CFISD appreciates global volunteers who invest in our community, and we appreciate your years of dedicated service to Swenke Elementary!

Congratulations to Marie Bordner, CFISD‚Äôs 2020 Outstanding Elementary Volunteer. CFISD believes in providing Opportunity for All, and volunteers help us to honor that promise.

Marie Bordner is a volunteer at Lowery Elementary several days a week. Marie prepares supplies for the school nurse, shelves books in the library and volunteers at book fairs. Marie is so well known in the clinic and library that students lovingly call her ‚ÄúMamaw.‚Äù She assists with special projects like Makerspace and lunch bunch book club several days a week.
Marie, CFISD is grateful for your service, and we appreciate the opportunities you help provide to our students!

Cy-Fair Nutrition Services
March 21 at 2:44 PM ¬∑

CURBSIDE MEAL SERVICE UPDATE: Begins March 23.

Cy-Fair Nutrition Services will provide FREE meals to children 18 & younger only during this period of school closure, beginning March 23. Grab & Go curbside meal pick-up only.

Hours: Breakfast and lunch available for pick up - 10:00AM - 1:00PM. Children must be present. No cash accepted. No adult meals.

Meal Sites:

Elementary: Bane, Danish, Francone, Frazier, Holbrook, Horne, Kirk

Middle: Arnold, Goodson, Thornton

High: Cy Creek, Cy Lakes, Cy Park, Cy Ridge, Cy Springs, Langham Creek

Cypress-Fairbanks ISD

Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 19 new photos.
February 27 at 8:56 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 CFISD Bond referendum, Harold R. Rowe Middle School (No. 19) will be located on the Westgreen multi-campus site next to Cypress Park HS. The $58,296,000 project is being constructed by Satterfield & Pontikes Construction and is slated for an August 2020 opening date.

The building includes a three-story academic wing with a centrally located and shared commons/kitchen building, along with a new football field and running track. This second facility of the master-planned multi-campus site designed by PBK Architects, consists of approximately 252,000 square feet and is designed to accommodate up to 1,750 students.

(Photos courtesy Multivista)

shared_text:
Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 12 new photos.
February 6 at 8:29 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)
text:
Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 12 new photos.
February 6 at 8:29 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)

shared_text:
Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 9 new photos.
January 30 at 8:16 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 CFISD Bond referendum, Harold R. Rowe Middle School (No. 19) will be located on the Westgreen multi-campus site next to Cypress Park HS. The $58,296,000 project is being constructed by Satterfield & Pontikes Construction and is slated for an August 2020 opening date.

The building includes a three-story academic wing with a centrally located and shared commons/kitchen building, along with a new football field and running track. This second facility of the master-planned multi-campus site designed by PBK Architects, consists of approximately 252,000 square feet and is designed to accommodate up to 1,750 students.

(Photos courtesy Multivista)

Funded by the 2014 CFISD Bond referendum, Harold R. Rowe Middle School (No. 19) will be located on the Westgreen multi-campus site next to Cypress Park HS. The $58,296,000 project is being constructed by Satterfield & Pontikes Construction and is slated for an August 2020 opening date.

The building includes a three-story academic wing with a centrally located and shared commons/kitchen building, along with a new football field and running track. This second facility of the master-planned multi-campus site designed by PBK Architects, consists of approximately 252,000 square feet and is designed to accommodate up to 1,750 students.

(Photos courtesy Multivista)

Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 8 new photos.
December 12, 2019 at 9:22 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)

Reminder: ticket sales continue today and tomorrow for Cy Creek's regional championship game against Katy Taylor (Saturday at 2 p.m. at NRG Stadium).

Purchase tickets at Cypress Creek HS (9815 Grant Road) in the athletic office today (Dec. 5) from 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. and tomorrow (Friday, Dec. 6) from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Tickets will also be sold in the cafeteria during lunch hours.

Tickets will also be available for purchase at the CFISD athletic office at the Berry Center (8877 Barker Cypress Road, entrance 2) from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. today and from 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. on Friday.

Cypress-Fairbanks ISD added 8 new photos.
November 21, 2019 at 7:55 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 Bond referendum, designed by Huckabee and constructed by DivisionOne Construction, the Hamilton MS renovation will be completed over two summers with final completion scheduled for the summer of 2020.

Renovation of the academic classrooms and library will be completed in summer 2019. Renovations in the classrooms and library consist of new lights, ceiling, casework and a fire sprinkler system. All restrooms in the academic portion of the building will be renovated.

Other items being renovated this summer include the front drives, staff/bus drives, building canopies, relocation of the service yard with a new cooling tower, academic area air-handling units, duct work and controls as well as a new detention pond between Hamilton MS and Hamilton ES. Also, the replacement of the roof has started and will be ongoing throughout the entire project.

(Photos courtesy Multivista Construction Documentation)

November 16, 2019 at 8:29 PM ¬∑ Sugar Land, TX ¬∑

The Cy-Fair HS volleyball team competed in the Region III-6A tournament Nov. 15-16 at Wheeler Fieldhouse in Sugar Land.

The Bobcats defeated Deer Park in three games (25-21, 25-20, 25-22) in the regional semifinal on Nov. 15, advancing to face Ridge Point in the regional final on Nov. 15.

Ridge Point defeated Cy-Fair, 3-0, in the regional championship match on Nov. 16 to end the Bobcats' season.

CFISD high school college and career specialists and advanced academics hosted the annual "Funding Your Future" night Nov. 13 at the Berry Center. The event gave seniors and their parents the opportunity to complete and learn about the free application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or the Texas Application for State Financial Aid (TASFA). Representatives from the Blinn College financial aid office were available in an on-site lab. It also included scholarship vendors and presentations.

November 14, 2019 at 8:25 AM ¬∑

Funded by the 2014 CFISD Bond referendum, Harold R. Rowe Middle School (No. 19) will be located on the Westgreen multi-campus site next to Cypress Park HS. The $58,296,000 project is being constructed by Satterfield & Pontikes Construction and is slated for an August 2020 opening date.

The building includes a three-story academic wing with a centrally located and shared commons/kitchen building, along with a new football field and running track. This second facility of the master-planned multi-campus site designed by PBK Architects, consists of approximately 252,000 square feet and is designed to accommodate up to 1,750 students.

(Photos courtesy Multivista)
